The bulletin contains statistical data on the work of enterprises with the types of activity "postal and courier activities" (GCTEA code 53) and "telecommunications" (GCTEA code 61), which reported on the statistical form of a 3-communication monthly frequency.

The bulletin contains the main indicators of postal and courier services and communication services. The work of communications enterprises is characterized by certain types of services provided, in monetary and in-kind terms, by regions, on the basis of reports submitted by enterprises.

Provision of communication services - the activity of communication operators, which consists in providing users with communication services listed in the general classifier of products of types of economic activity. Volume Communication Services includes Volume intercity, international and local telephony services, data transmission, the Internet, mobile communications, program distribution, and other telecommunication services.
Postal activity - the provision of postal services through postal networks.
Courier mail services - postal services for the transportation and delivery of postal items, provided using a courier.
Volume of communication services - accrued funds for communications rendered Services by population, enterprises and organizations, regardless of the payment term.
